under the following conditions:

1. Attribution
Any use, distribution, publication or citation
must clearly and visibly credit the author:
Raiko Pulvermacher

2. Transparency of Derivatives
If the material is modified, extended or embedded into other contexts,
it must be clearly stated that it is a derived work.

3. Research & Publications
If this work is used as a basis for:
– scientific research
– experiments
– simulations
– publications
– preprints
– talks

the author must be informed prior to or at the latest upon publication.

Co-authorship is expected when this work
contributes substantially to the research question, structure or interpretation.
Final authorship decisions remain subject to the rules of the respective publication venue.

4. Non-Exclusivity
This license does not claim ownership of results,
but requires transparency, acknowledgment and participation.

5. Disclaimer
This work does not represent a physical theory, formal model,
or verified scientific claim.
It is provided without warranty.

Use is at your own risk.

6. License Continuity
Derived works must retain this license or an equivalent license with the same intent.
